Sass stands for Syntactically Awesome Stylesheet.
Sass is an extension to CSS.
Sass is a CSS pre-processor.
Sass reduces repetition of CSS.

Note - Browser does not understand Sass code, we need a Sass pre-processor to convert Sass code into standard CSS.

Sass files has the ".scss" file extension.
Multiline comment - /* comment */
Singleline comment - // comment

Programming language - Sass is based on Ruby






